---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import BreadcrumbSchema from '../components/schema/BreadcrumbSchema.astro';
import { SITE } from '../consts';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="Underdial privacy policy — what data we collect, how it is used, and how to delete it. No account, no sign-in, data stays on your device."
  path="/privacy"
>
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <BreadcrumbSchema crumbs={[{ name: 'Privacy Policy', url: `${SITE.url}/privacy` }]} />
  </Fragment>

  <p class="brand">{SITE.name}</p>
  <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p class="effective">Effective Date: June 14, 2026</p>

  <p>
    Underdial ("we", "our", or "the app") is a watch-advisor app for iOS, with a
    companion website at <a href={SITE.url}>{SITE.url}</a>. This policy explains
    what we collect, how we use it, and how to delete it &mdash; for both the app
    and the website. The short version: there is no account and no sign-in, and
    your collection data stays on your device.
  </p>

  <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
  <p>
    <strong>No account.</strong> Underdial has no sign-in and no user accounts.
    We do not collect your name, email, or any login identifier to use the app.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>On-device content.</strong> The watches in your box, your wrist size,
    your preferences, and your check history are stored locally on your device.
    This data is not uploaded to us and is not associated with any identity.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Device data.</strong> We may collect basic, anonymous diagnostics
    (OS version, device model, app version) and crash reports to keep the app
    working. We do not collect precise location, contacts, health, or financial
    data.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Purchase information.</strong> Underdial Plus subscriptions are
    processed by Apple through the App Store. We receive a purchase confirmation
    but never see your payment details.
  </p>

  <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>To run your box, wrist-fit settings, and check history on your device.</li>
    <li>To produce verdicts, redundancy flags, cheaper-alternative lists, and Box Audits locally.</li>
    <li>To keep the catalog current and the app stable using anonymous diagnostics.</li>
    <li>To process Underdial Plus subscriptions through the App Store.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>3. Privacy Posture</h2>
  <p>
    Your box, wrist notes, and check history are <strong>private by default</strong>
    and live on your device. We do not run cross-user advertising, and we do not
    sell personal information.
  </p>

  <h2>4. Third-Party Services</h2>
  <p>
    We rely on a small number of third parties. Each receives only the data
    necessary for the service it provides:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Apple</strong> &mdash; App Store distribution and subscription payment processing.</li>
    <li><strong>Awin</strong> &mdash; affiliate network that powers the outbound "Buy from" retailer links.</li>
    <li><strong>Anonymous analytics and crash reporting</strong> &mdash; aggregate, non-identifying usage and stability data.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>5. Affiliate Link Tracking</h2>
  <p>
    When you tap a "Buy from" link, Underdial sends you to the retailer through
    our affiliate network, Awin. The retailer and Awin may set cookies or
    identifiers on the destination site that we have no control over. Underdial
    itself does not pass any personal identity to the retailer &mdash; there is
    none to pass.
  </p>

  <h2>6. Data Retention</h2>
  <p>
    Because your collection data lives on your device, it is retained for as
    long as the app is installed. Deleting the app, or using the in-app reset,
    permanently removes your box, wrist settings, and check history. There is
    nothing stored on our servers to delete.
  </p>

  <h2>7. Your Rights</h2>
  <p>
    California residents and EU users have rights under CCPA and GDPR
    respectively. Because we do not hold an identifiable copy of your collection
    data, most data-access and deletion requests are satisfied directly on your
    device. For any question, contact us using the address below.
  </p>

  <h2>8. Children's Privacy</h2>
  <p>
    Underdial is not directed to children under 13. We do not knowingly collect
    information from anyone under 13.
  </p>

  <h2>9. Data Security</h2>
  <p>
    Network requests are made over HTTPS. Your collection data is stored on your
    device using the operating system's standard app storage. We follow
    industry-standard practices to protect any anonymous data we handle.
  </p>

  <h2>10. How to Delete Your Data</h2>
  <p>You may remove your data at any time:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>In-app:</strong> Settings &rarr; Reset Data.</li>
    <li><strong>Delete the app:</strong> removing Underdial from your device deletes its local data.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>See the <a href="/delete-account">Delete Your Data</a> page for the full walkthrough.</p>

  <h2>11. Changes to This Policy</h2>
  <p>
    We may update this policy from time to time. Material changes will be
    communicated through the app. Continued use after changes constitutes
    acceptance.
  </p>

  <h2>12. Contact</h2>
  <p>
    For questions about this privacy policy or your data, contact us at:
    <a href={`mailto:${SITE.supportEmail}`}>{SITE.supportEmail}</a>
  </p>

  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
